threads = [
{"threadId": "14be8c4730893b97", "messages": [
{"messageId": "14be8c4730893b97", "headers": {"From": "Darshan agarwal <agarwal.darshan95@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 3 Mar 2015 02:01:29 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "I am a 3rd year CS student interested in NLP. I am interested in the Reference Resolution project. Can I know which projects in NLP can be opted for GSoC 2015?"},
{"messageId": "14be8e5bc55ea1b5", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Thu, 5 Mar 2015 15:45:43 +0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "See the shiny new up to date GSoC 2015 Ideas page."},
{"messageId": "14bf4eebd5b6e836", "headers": {"From": "Darshan agarwal <agarwal.darshan95@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sat, 7 Mar 2015 07:50:57 -0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "I want to contribute on the project Unsupervised Language Learning. I am particularly interested in Morphology and Disjunct extraction, parse ranking."},
{"messageId": "14bf538953ea1a9b", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sat, 7 Mar 2015 11:11:18 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "What languages do you know well enough to read and write? Well enough to understand their morphology?"},
{"messageId": "14bf6ba7a8a8623a", "headers": {"From": "Darshan agarwal <agarwal.darshan95@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sun, 8 Mar 2015 05:43:09 +0530", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "I know English and Hindi well enough."},
{"messageId": "14bf7a9c161f896d", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sat, 7 Mar 2015 22:34:09 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] GSOC 2015 NLP"}, "body": "We have someone else working on the syntax-learning pieces, but no one working on morphology learning. English morphology is not really worth pursuing. In order to determine if the morphology work is going well, you would have to actually look at it, and see if what it is generating matches what it should be."}
]},
{"threadId": "14bbdbf2bfa0e014", "messages": [
{"messageId": "14bbdbf2bfa0e014", "headers": {"From": "Curtis M. Faith <curtis.m.faith@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 24 Feb 2015 14:39:54 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] Opencog coding and development standards while editing existing code"}, "body": "I find it nontrivially more difficult to quickly parse new code when coding style around control statements is not consistent. Much of the existing code does not follow the development standards. What should we do with existing code? Fix whole file before a Pull Request? Fix only functions we touch?"},
{"messageId": "14bbde7382593bf7", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 24 Feb 2015 17:23:19 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: Opencog coding and development standards"}, "body": "Please do not change whitespace. Except maybe for the missing whitespace after control statements."},
{"messageId": "14bbdfd3cb2e7b4c", "headers": {"From": "Curtis Faith <curtis.m.faith@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 24 Feb 2015 18:47:42 -0500", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: Opencog coding and development standards"}, "body": "Sorry for the confusion, I am not proposing changing whitespace in existing files except for control statements. I was only asking about code that I write myself."},
{"messageId": "14bbe02541e34bc2", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 24 Feb 2015 17:52:57 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: Opencog coding and development standards"}, "body": "Ideally, follow the style that is established in the current file."},
{"messageId": "14bbfb087e4b627b", "headers": {"From": "Nil Geisweiller <ngeiswei@googlemail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 25 Feb 2015 08:43:06 +0100", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: Opencog coding and development standards"}, "body": "I have added a line about space between if and ( on the wiki. I personally feel both brace styles are OK. During a debate I browsed the code of about two dozen projects, coding standards are very poorly respected in large projects. If you wish to replace all if/for/while( by if/for/while (, I do not think that would bother anyone."}
]},
{"threadId": "14ad8457679bf71f", "messages": [
{"messageId": "14ad8457679bf71f", "headers": {"From": "Amartya Sanyal <amartya18x@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sun, 4 Jan 2015 10:16:41 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "I am willing to do a project under OpenCog in GSoC 2015. I have done work in Machine Learning, face recognition, neural networks."},
{"messageId": "14ada96c8b9bc95d", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Sun, 11 Jan 2015 14:01:41 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "The opencog wiki has a page called Ideas which lists various things. Re: face recognition: what, currently, is the best open-source library for face detection and face recognition in live video? Any chance that its wrapped up in a ROS node?"},
{"messageId": "14adb27ea21f9a64", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Sun, 11 Jan 2015 16:40:32 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "I would be very happy to supervise a project using and further developing Py-DeSTIN for object recognition, or face recognition. Extending the frequent subtree mining on DeSTIN trees code that Ted Sanders wrote last year to pyDeSTIN interests me particularly."},
{"messageId": "14ae7a46efbf437b", "headers": {"From": "Amartya Sanyal <amartya18x@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 14 Jan 2015 00:51:59 -0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "I was actually thinking in terms of hybrid networks. Something that is highly customizable and can be adapted according to the task. I have experience with Convolutional Neural Networks."},
{"messageId": "14ae9d62c2e45681", "headers": {"From": "Amartya Sanyal <amartya18x@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 14 Jan 2015 11:05:33 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] Re: projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "Using DeSTIN and SVM or Neural Nets to Effectively Classify Images is one that certainly interests me."},
{"messageId": "14ae9d930b906025", "headers": {"From": "Amartya Sanyal <amartya18x@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 14 Jan 2015 11:08:51 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] Re: projects for GSoC 2015"}, "body": "We can actually include the feature extraction mechanism within DeSTIN so that it can work on raw data. Convolutional Neural Nets perform this task gracefully."}
]},
{"threadId": "151f4546cdcad98e", "messages": [
{"messageId": "151f4546cdcad98e", "headers": {"From": "ankit kumar <ankitkr710@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 30 Dec 2015 11:19:10 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] New Developer [please help :)]"}, "body": "I am Ankit Kumar from IIT Guwahati, interested in contributing to OpenCog. I have taken Machine Learning and Data Mining courses. I have experience with clustering algorithms. How should I get started if I wish to contribute in C++?"},
{"messageId": "151f45ba85b2c071", "headers": {"From": "ankit kumar <ankitkr710@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 30 Dec 2015 11:27:04 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] Re: New Developer [please help :)]"}, "body": "It appears there is clustering related work. Can somebody help me out with the starting point for it?"},
{"messageId": "151f68b5adf3037f", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Wed, 30 Dec 2015 23:38:06 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: New Developer [please help :)]"}, "body": "The thing to do is to review the wiki Ideas page and see if one of these tickles your fancy, and might be something you could make progress with."},
{"messageId": "151f6a95e22d9151", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Thu, 31 Dec 2015 14:11:12 +0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: New Developer [please help :)]"}, "body": "My idea is to implement agglomerative clustering using the URE (Unified Rule Engine). To work in this direction, you should learn to use the Pattern Matcher and the URE. I would suggest to do this in a mix of Scheme and C++; you should become familiar with the OpenCog Scheme shell."},
{"messageId": "151f734296ff3c66", "headers": {"From": "ankit kumar <ankitkr710@gmail.com>", "Date": "Thu, 31 Dec 2015 00:42:47 -0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Re: New Developer [please help :)]"}, "body": "Thanks! I would like to work on this idea. I would do this in Scheme and C++. I am going through the tutorials and setting up the Scheme shell."}
]}
]

